create vpc- 12.0.0.0/16
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
We are going to create 2 public subnets.

1.crtete subnet- name-testpublic-vpc-a - select vpc which we created - subnet range -12.0.1.0/24- select zone a
2.crtete subnet- name-testpublic-vpc-b - select vpc which we created - subnet range -12.0.2.0/24 - select zone b
 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
IG - create it - attach to the VPC which we have created  
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
setup route table - name - test-rt-public 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
subnet association - edit - select subnets -save association then go to route - edit - add - 
0.0.0.0/0 - choose the IG that we have created -save. 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
crte ec2 - test-ec2 - t2.micro -network setting - select vpc - subnet 1a - public ip -enable 
add SG - HTTP -SOURCE type - anywhere
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#!/bin/bash

yes | sudo apt update
yes | sudo apt install apache2

# Create an index.html file with server details
echo "<h1>Server Details</h1>
<p><strong>Hostname:</strong> $(hostname)</p>
<p><strong>IP Address:</strong> $(hostname -I | cut -d' ' -f1)</p>" | sudo tee /var/www/html/index.html

# Restart Apache service
sudo systemctl restart
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
access it
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Set up load balancer - TG - first select http only.  
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
set up route table (NOTE - keep the domain as it is, do not add a subdomain) -  
crete hosted zone - add record - access it by domain  - which will be http 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Now go to ACM - ADD domain - create record - allow alis - select ALB - keep 60 sec -region select - select alb. 
Then go to ALB - add rule - create rule for https - select the domain over there - then access it, which will be https 
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
